Thoughts on the diabetic journey... It’s Sunday morning, the beginning of a new week. Many of us look ahead to the next few days and plan on what we will be doing. We set goals. Goals are important in life but too often we set fairly ambiguous goals. “I will eat healthier” is broad. “I will add 1/2 c of veggies to my dinner plate each day” is specific. A good way to goal set is to use the acronym MAPS. M- measurable  A- attainable  P- positive S- specific It doesn’t matter the goal - if it can be a goal it can succeed.  Happy journeying

I am here as a caregiver to both of my parents whom suffer due to diabetes and my son whom is a cancer survivor and suffers due to chemotherapy that damaged his nerves. They have all been on Gabapentin. Some doses higher then others and on it for longer. They are unhappy with it and we are looking for alternative treatments and coping strategies. Im so so frustrated and depressed over the tingling in my right upper back!! This started 5 days after a kenalog (steroid) shot in my hip area....everyone keeps telling me it cant be from shot that i would of felt symptoms immediately not 5 days post shot. And they also said give the med time to get out of your system, about 35 days...umm its been almost 6 mos now 😞. I just want my old physical life back....never had this pain or any pain really since before 3/28!! I was normal...ive had neck and thoracic mris (7/30) thinking that would show something, im a RN so it did not really show much maybe i will get more info at appt on Monday. This stuff sucks!! I am just blown away that a shot could of caused this but it had to have?? What else could it of been?! I was literally fine prior to that shot and it is everyday just constant tingling in right upper back only then it gets tight feeling. Please tell me if anyone is in my boat...i have never liked meds and find myself using nsaids more than i want as im also recovering from CT surgery 5 weeks ago... will this ever just go away or lessen?! Im desperate and have been researching alot on Herbal or natural products but have no clue...most docs never want to advise on that stuff either just wants to push script meds. I think im gonna demand PT and a specialist?! Idk what do yall think? Note: i had mri couple yrs back (2016)  on neck that showed bulging discs and stenosis was mentioned. I can put results in comment below if needed. The unknown is killing me...like what exactly is my diagnosis and how do i correct it?! ( docs need to answer) Thanks for listening.. and i will continue to pray for a miracle 😭😭😭😭

Well I had a good doctor appointment yesterday with my new endocrinologist.  He was very pleased with my meter readings and my average number was 119.  He took me off of Glipizide so now I just take the Metformin.  He said if I had three good averages he would take me off all medicines.  I lost 10 # .  So that sure is an incentive to keep going.  Just wish I could find a place to swim as I belong to our local YMCA but the pool is only open for laps.  Guess I could use the exercise room but I'd much rather swim.
